[
    {
        "text": "Now, to an international report which says that human action...",
        "startTime": 400,
        "endTime": 4086,
        "slowStartTime": 750,
        "slowEndTime": 6354
    },
    {
        "text": "...to save the ozone layer appears to have worked.",
        "startTime": 4159,
        "endTime": 6655,
        "slowStartTime": 6388,
        "slowEndTime": 10208
    },
    {
        "text": "The study says it should fully recover within decades...",
        "startTime": 7010,
        "endTime": 9861,
        "slowStartTime": 10665,
        "slowEndTime": 15016
    },
    {
        "text": "...as Naomi Choi Smith now reports.",
        "startTime": 10161,
        "endTime": 12826,
        "slowStartTime": 15391,
        "slowEndTime": 19464
    },
    {
        "text": "The ozone layer, a thin shield that protects us...",
        "startTime": 13424,
        "endTime": 16730,
        "slowStartTime": 20286,
        "slowEndTime": 25320
    },
    {
        "text": "...from the sun's harmful ultraviolet rays,...",
        "startTime": 16820,
        "endTime": 19148,
        "slowStartTime": 25380,
        "slowEndTime": 28947
    },
    {
        "text": "...damaged and depleted by chemicals released into the atmosphere.",
        "startTime": 19459,
        "endTime": 22891,
        "slowStartTime": 29338,
        "slowEndTime": 34562
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, finally some good news.",
        "startTime": 23453,
        "endTime": 25578,
        "slowStartTime": 35330,
        "slowEndTime": 38592
    },
    {
        "text": "The ozone layer is healing and could be fully restored in the next four decades.",
        "startTime": 26061,
        "endTime": 31030,
        "slowStartTime": 39242,
        "slowEndTime": 46770
    },
    {
        "text": "That's according to a new report co-authored by the UN, U.S., and EU...",
        "startTime": 31766,
        "endTime": 35937,
        "slowStartTime": 47799,
        "slowEndTime": 54130
    },
    {
        "text": "...which says, human action to ban ozone harming chemicals is working.",
        "startTime": 36453,
        "endTime": 40894,
        "slowStartTime": 54830,
        "slowEndTime": 61566
    },
    {
        "text": "The phase out of nearly 99% of banned ozone depleting substances...",
        "startTime": 41271,
        "endTime": 45922,
        "slowStartTime": 62057,
        "slowEndTime": 69108
    },
    {
        "text": "...has succeeded in safeguarding the ozone layer,...",
        "startTime": 46407,
        "endTime": 48768,
        "slowStartTime": 69761,
        "slowEndTime": 73377
    },
    {
        "text": "...leading to notable recovery of the ozone layer in the upper stratosphere...",
        "startTime": 48847,
        "endTime": 53160,
        "slowStartTime": 73421,
        "slowEndTime": 79965
    },
    {
        "text": "...and decreased human exposure to harmful ultraviolet rays from the Sun.",
        "startTime": 53233,
        "endTime": 57661,
        "slowStartTime": 80000,
        "slowEndTime": 86716
    },
    {
        "text": "Holes were first discovered in the ozone layer in the 1980s.",
        "startTime": 58373,
        "endTime": 61631,
        "slowStartTime": 87710,
        "slowEndTime": 92672
    },
    {
        "text": "By 1987, 46 countries had signed up to the Montreal Protocol,...",
        "startTime": 61934,
        "endTime": 66619,
        "slowStartTime": 93051,
        "slowEndTime": 100153
    },
    {
        "text": "...banning gases in aerosols and fridges called CFCs.",
        "startTime": 67084,
        "endTime": 70621,
        "slowStartTime": 100776,
        "slowEndTime": 106157
    },
    {
        "text": "They were destroying the ozone letting through harmful ultraviolet rays...",
        "startTime": 71003,
        "endTime": 75139,
        "slowStartTime": 106655,
        "slowEndTime": 112933
    },
    {
        "text": "...that can cause problems like skin cancer.",
        "startTime": 75211,
        "endTime": 77451,
        "slowStartTime": 112967,
        "slowEndTime": 116401
    },
    {
        "text": "But while the depletion of ozone is not a major cause of climate change,...",
        "startTime": 78116,
        "endTime": 81947,
        "slowStartTime": 117324,
        "slowEndTime": 123146
    },
    {
        "text": "...saving the ozone layer does have a positive knock-on effect on global warming,...",
        "startTime": 82297,
        "endTime": 86581,
        "slowStartTime": 123596,
        "slowEndTime": 130096
    },
    {
        "text": "...because some of the chemicals that were phased out are powerful greenhouse gases.",
        "startTime": 87089,
        "endTime": 91573,
        "slowStartTime": 130784,
        "slowEndTime": 137585
    },
    {
        "text": "The report says the ozone layer should recover to 1980 levels...",
        "startTime": 92128,
        "endTime": 95959,
        "slowStartTime": 138342,
        "slowEndTime": 144163
    },
    {
        "text": "...by roughly 2066 over the Antarctic, by 2045 over the Arctic,...",
        "startTime": 96064,
        "endTime": 101420,
        "slowStartTime": 144246,
        "slowEndTime": 152355
    },
    {
        "text": "...and by 2040 for the rest of the world.",
        "startTime": 101777,
        "endTime": 104409,
        "slowStartTime": 152816,
        "slowEndTime": 156839
    },
    {
        "text": "There's always the risk that progress could be reversed.",
        "startTime": 105069,
        "endTime": 107923,
        "slowStartTime": 157753,
        "slowEndTime": 162110
    },
    {
        "text": "Still the UN is optimistic, saying this sets a good example...",
        "startTime": 108453,
        "endTime": 112223,
        "slowStartTime": 162830,
        "slowEndTime": 168560
    },
    {
        "text": "...for other environmental action as the battle for our planet's future isn't over yet.",
        "startTime": 112305,
        "endTime": 117854,
        "slowStartTime": 168607,
        "slowEndTime": 177006
    },
    {
        "text": "Naomi Choi Smith, BBC News.",
        "startTime": 118271,
        "endTime": 120320,
        "slowStartTime": 177556,
        "slowEndTime": 180705
    }
]